commentTextItems.html: hits it high in the air down the ground to long on and taken by Holder.

commentPostTextItems.html: West Indies win by 52 runs and clinches a place in the Super Six. Joyce and both the O'Brien brothers kept them in the game, but Ireland lost wickets at regular intervals, which put them on the back foot. Powell is the Man-of-the-Match for his 100, a wonderful knock. Thanks for tuning in, do join us for the next game.

stories.title: Rovman Powell ton leads West Indies into Super Six
stories.subTitle: Ireland v West Indies, World Cup Qualifiers, Harare
stories.seoTitle: Rovman Powell ton leads West Indies into Super Six
stories.summary: From 83 for 5, West Indies recovered to set Ireland a target of 258, and proceeded to win by 52 runs with Kemar Roach picking up four vital wickets
